n important event that happened to me this weekend. I am sharing this with as many people as I can, since I am very excited. I would also invite everyone else to share something inspirational. I believe this area of the board is a fitting place to share given the heavy topic matter. (We can all use good news or a break!)   <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><br>All of you are familiar with me through my avatar Lurikeen. Lurikeen is a Necro and is far different than who I am as a RL person (not so obivous to some, hence the needed clarification). I play EQ as an escape from reality not to expand reality... at any rate let me get to my story.<br><br>I am a Networking professional in RL and my job can be very stressful. Not only that, I am married and have two children and while I love them dearly they, too, can add to stress. To manage stress I used to practice martial arts. Up to three years ago I had practiced Jeet Kune Do (a non-traditional form of Wing Chun) meditatively, but I had a change in careers and focused on the career and dropped martial arts all together. Something I dearly love. Well, the consequence has been 3 years of feeling agitated and frustrated and not knowing why... so I decided to end it all.<br><br>No! I didn't opt for suicide. Instead, I had myself what some call an &quot;Ah, ha&quot; moment. Through introspection I began uncovering what things I had dropped for my career and the list began to get very long. Sure, I have been taking time to play an enjoyable game (EQ), but it isn't at all as satisfying as the things I used to do such as home brewing, martial arts, and spending more time with my family.<br><br>So, through introspection the &quot;ah, ha!&quot; moment came and this is how it happened. I was thinking about drawing a black dot on a window with a marker then asking myself what I see. Of course, I see both a black dot and the world beyond it framed in the window. BANG! I intellectualized why I have an &quot;open mind&quot;. I had patted myself on the back that I hadn't given notice to just the black dot or to just the window, etc. but that I had &quot;seen&quot; it all together as a whole. Well, not really. <br><br>It hit me like a ton of bricks... I understood that I didn't &quot;see&quot; anything at all. I had cognized an event from the visual, but still missed the mark! I wasn't seeing what things are of themselves. I hadn't allowed things to just be. I was being to active in shaping my world and not really being a participant in my world. Just as I viewed the black dot and the world beyond the window I didn't &quot;see&quot; me there, too.<br><br>The lesson I learned was to take steps to stop mourning my losses (like not doing martial arts) and accept what I am in the world today. Rather than try to be the master of my reality, I have refreshed my view that I am a participant in reality. It isn't mine to shape, but I sure as hell can be part of it! You know what. I feel damn good.<br><br>Again, I am sharing this experience everywhere I can, since it might strike a cord with others. Please share whatever has inspired you of late. If you must flame... oh, well.<br><br>Further, wouldn't it be great if most of the people of the world could see them selves as participants in the world rather than masters of it? <br> <p><center><font face="arial" color="CCFFFF">Lurikeen Mali'Kyre</FONT></center><center><table style='Filter: Shadow(Color=#150517, Direction=225)'><tr><td><span class='Necromancer'><font size=2 color="red" face="arial"><i>NECROMANCER</span></td></tr></table></font></i></center><center><font face=arial></center><center><I>"My eyes will pierce your soul, then I will take your life!"</I></center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/ubrutas222.showPublicProfile?l